AngloGold, Impala, Imperial Could Move: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-02-17T05:50:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/anglogold-impala-imperial-could-move-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell for a
second day, losing 282.16, or 0.9 percent, to 32,778.12 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG SJ): The world’s third largest
gold producer releases fourth-quarter earnings. Shares in the
company fell 70 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 332.30 rand.    Distell Group Ltd . (DST SJ): Jan Scannell, the liquor
producer’s managing director, said the company sees a difficult
period ahead as it faces increased competition from  SABMiller
Plc  and  Diageo Plc . Distell fell 3.25 rand, or 4.2 percent, to
74 rand.    Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd . (IMP SJ): The world’s second-
largest platinum producer announces first-half earnings. Shares
in the company dropped 1.77 rand, or 0.8 percent, to 213.50
rand.    Imperial Holdings Ltd . (IPL SJ): Freight workers will
continue their strike for a fourth day. Protesters stoned and
looted trucks and delivery vans in Gauteng’s East Rand area
yesterday. Imperial, which operates haulage trucks, gained 67
cents, or 0.6 percent, to 111.59 rand.  Woolworths Holdings Ltd. (WHL SJ): The South African food
and clothing retailer said first-half net income rose 17 percent
to 775 million rand ($107 million). The company’s shares fell 1
cent, or less than 0.1 percent, to 24.60 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) gained 0.8 percent to $26.80.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd . (AU US) gained 0.8 percent to $46.26. BHP
Billiton Plc (BBL US) dropped 1.3 percent to $79.69. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) rose 0.9 percent to $4.59. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) jumped 2.6 percent to $16.58. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) added 1.4 percent to $11.04. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) gained 0.7 percent to $29.25. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) rose 1.5
percent to $5.34. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) declined 0.7 percent to
$50.82.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
